1
00:00:50,960 --> 00:00:51,640
Mom!

2
00:00:53,320 --> 00:00:56,000
Mom! Mom!

3
00:00:56,439 --> 00:00:58,799
Mom! Mom! Mom!

4
00:00:59,560 --> 00:01:00,640
Family members, please step back. Mom!

5
00:01:03,039 --> 00:01:03,920
Mom!

6
00:01:07,120 --> 00:01:10,719
Mom! Mom! Mom!

7
00:01:12,040 --> 00:01:13,319
Mom!

8
00:01:39,560 --> 00:01:40,640
Found the bleeding point.

9
00:01:41,079 --> 00:01:42,400
It's a fairly thick branch artery.

10
00:01:42,719 --> 00:01:44,079
Rare to see one in this area.

11
00:01:44,840 --> 00:01:45,439
Stop the bleeding.

12
00:01:47,319 --> 00:01:48,159
What are you staring at?

13
00:01:48,760 --> 00:01:49,599
Hemostat.

14
00:01:53,599 --> 00:01:54,439
Examining the vessel.

15
00:02:42,919 --> 00:02:44,840
Is this how you performed surgeries back in Pingjin?

16
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:46,039
Who taught you that?

17
00:02:47,520 --> 00:02:49,400
The OR is no place to play hero.

18
00:02:50,039 --> 00:02:51,280
Just do your own job.

19
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:20,599
Dr. Jiang, that move you pulled was incredible.

20
00:03:20,719 --> 00:03:21,560
Come on, teach me.

21
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:23,199
Being helpful is a good thing.

22
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:25,280
But arrogance in the wrong setting...

23
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:27,000
that's just causing trouble.

24
00:03:28,439 --> 00:03:29,199
Dr. Jiang.

25
00:03:29,919 --> 00:03:30,800
Be more careful next time.

26
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:33,599
Dr. Chen, no offense, but...

27
00:03:33,840 --> 00:03:34,840
sometimes, you really...

28
00:03:34,919 --> 00:03:36,280
need to learn a thing or two from me.

29
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:37,919
Be more open-minded.

30
00:03:38,080 --> 00:03:39,240
You're the big shot of pediatric dentistry.

31
00:03:39,599 --> 00:03:40,840
Naturally, you're in an unbeatable position.

32
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:42,599
Coaxing kids, sure...

33
00:03:43,080 --> 00:03:44,000
I'm no match for you.

34
00:03:47,240 --> 00:03:47,879
Fine.

35
00:03:48,039 --> 00:03:48,840
You think you're so capable.

36
00:03:49,039 --> 00:03:49,639
But up on that operating table,

37
00:03:49,719 --> 00:03:51,039
you can't even keep your own heart rate steady.

38
00:03:51,479 --> 00:03:52,960
Dr. Jiang, I still admire you.

39
00:03:56,280 --> 00:03:57,840
I emailed you the last treatment plan.

40
00:03:58,000 --> 00:03:58,759
Remember to check it.

41
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:00,479
Dr. Jiang.

42
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:03,639
I dragged you into today's mess.

43
00:04:03,759 --> 00:04:04,919
Say whatever you want about me,

44
00:04:05,199 --> 00:04:06,319
but could you please...

45
00:04:09,479 --> 00:04:10,639
I'm not finished yet.

46
00:04:16,759 --> 00:04:17,399
I have no reason to keep secrets

47
00:04:17,480 --> 00:04:18,920
for an unprofessional doctor.

48
00:04:19,240 --> 00:04:21,000
If you can't overcome your own psychological issues,

49
00:04:21,199 --> 00:04:21,959
change careers while you still can.

50
00:04:22,240 --> 00:04:23,279
Don't hold the team back,

51
00:04:23,519 --> 00:04:25,199
and don't gamble with patients' lives.

52
00:04:38,879 --> 00:04:39,600
Get in.

53
00:04:56,120 --> 00:04:59,160
Tang Yi, you've got this.

54
00:05:17,839 --> 00:05:19,079
Thanks for bringing me here.

55
00:05:19,439 --> 00:05:20,879
I haven't felt this relaxed in ages.

56
00:05:22,800 --> 00:05:24,360
I brought you here to clear your head,

57
00:05:25,079 --> 00:05:26,160
not to hang out with you.

58
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:28,160
Tough talk, soft heart.

59
00:05:29,040 --> 00:05:29,959
You just have to put on

60
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:32,319
an icy, unapproachable persona. Aren't you tired?

61
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:38,600
Psychology says

62
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:40,639
there's a specific term for your behavior.

63
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:42,879
It's called Alexithymia.

64
00:05:43,439 --> 00:05:45,920
It means you clearly have emotions inside,

65
00:05:46,279 --> 00:05:47,279
but you can't express them.

66
00:05:47,439 --> 00:05:48,560
You always hide and bottle them up,

67
00:05:48,959 --> 00:05:49,800
causing misunderstandings.

68
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:54,279
You sure dabble in a lot of things.

69
00:05:56,160 --> 00:05:57,480
The book also says

70
00:05:57,800 --> 00:06:00,279
it's often because in childhood,

71
00:06:00,519 --> 00:06:02,439
you lacked love and communication.

72
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:03,199
You never know

73
00:06:03,279 --> 00:06:05,199
how to properly express your feelings.

74
00:06:05,439 --> 00:06:08,120
You're used to hiding your true self.

75
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:18,439
Your ex-girlfriend?

76
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:19,920
Why aren't you picking up?

77
00:06:20,040 --> 00:06:20,959
Mind your own business.

78
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:23,160
Watch out, or you'll fall into the sea.

79
00:06:24,759 --> 00:06:26,040
Psychology also says

80
00:06:26,360 --> 00:06:27,439
when someone deliberately keeps

81
00:06:27,560 --> 00:06:28,600
their distance from another,

82
00:06:28,680 --> 00:06:29,839
it's not out of dislike,

83
00:06:30,360 --> 00:06:31,519
but out of avoidance.

84
00:06:32,920 --> 00:06:33,639
Dr. Jiang,

85
00:06:34,279 --> 00:06:35,240
which type are you?

86
00:06:40,439 --> 00:06:41,120
Grandma!

87
00:06:44,160 --> 00:06:44,839
Grandma!

88
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:52,720
Family members, please wait outside.

89
00:07:16,360 --> 00:07:17,079
Daniel.

90
00:07:42,439 --> 00:07:43,759
Can you stay a bit longer?

91
00:08:19,199 --> 00:08:20,199
I'm sorry.

92
00:08:46,440 --> 00:08:47,600
I think I belong

93
00:08:49,240 --> 00:08:50,000
to the third kind,

94
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:53,759
the kind who can't let go of an Obsession.

95
00:09:24,399 --> 00:09:26,159
If an Obsession were that easy to let go of,

96
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:28,320
it wouldn't be called an Obsession.

97
00:09:49,480 --> 00:09:50,919
Brushing your teeth is a daily routine.

98
00:09:51,120 --> 00:09:52,759
But is your toothbrush really clean?

99
00:09:52,960 --> 00:09:55,360
An expired toothbrush is a breeding ground for bacteria.

100
00:09:55,519 --> 00:09:57,360
It not only greatly reduces brushing effectiveness,

101
00:09:57,639 --> 00:09:59,840
but can also cause swollen, bleeding gums,

102
00:09:59,960 --> 00:10:01,240
and a host of other oral health issues.

103
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:02,639
For the sake of your oral health,

104
00:10:02,720 --> 00:10:05,200
we recommend replacing your toothbrush every three months.
